# helper function for visualization
show_digit = function(arr784, col = gray(12:1 / 12), ...) {
  image(matrix(as.matrix(arr784[-785]), nrow = 28)[, 28:1], col = col, ...)
}

# load image files
load_image_file = function(filename) {
  ret = list()
  f = file(filename, 'rb')
  readBin(f, 'integer', n = 1, size = 4, endian = 'big')
  n    = readBin(f, 'integer', n = 1, size = 4, endian = 'big')
  nrow = readBin(f, 'integer', n = 1, size = 4, endian = 'big')
  ncol = readBin(f, 'integer', n = 1, size = 4, endian = 'big')
  x = readBin(f, 'integer', n = n * nrow * ncol, size = 1, signed = FALSE)
  close(f)
  data.frame(matrix(x, ncol = nrow * ncol, byrow = TRUE))
}

# load label files
load_label_file = function(filename) {
  f = file(filename, 'rb')
  readBin(f, 'integer', n = 1, size = 4, endian = 'big')
  n = readBin(f, 'integer', n = 1, size = 4, endian = 'big')
  y = readBin(f, 'integer', n = n, size = 1, signed = FALSE)
  close(f)
  y
}

PART2

kmeans = function(digits, n_clusters, initializations){
  set.seed(12)
  # define parameters
  #n_clusters = 10
  #initializations = 25
  #init = 1
  library(rpgm)
  iterations = 100
  # define data
  # test data
  #digitsx <- rbind(matrix(rnorm(100, mean= 10, sd = 1), ncol = 2),
  #           matrix(rnorm(100, mean = 14, sd = 1), ncol = 2),
  #           matrix(rnorm(100, mean = 16, sd = 1), ncol = 2)) 
  #digitsx <- t(digitsx)
  digitsx = digits
  dim_x1 = dim(digitsx)[1]
  dim_x2 = dim(digitsx)[2]
  minLoss = c(rep((10^10), initializations))
  for (init in 1:initializations){
    #print(init)
    iter=0
    loss_dist = c(rep(0,iterations))
    loss_diff = 100
    avg_loss_diff = 100
    #initialize cluster mean and distances
    random_sample = sample(1:dim_x2-(2*n_clusters),1, replace=FALSE)
    cluster_mean = digitsx[,1:n_clusters] 
    cluster_dist = matrix(c(rep(0,dim_x2*n_clusters)), ncol=n_clusters)
    cluster_label = c(sample(1:n_clusters, dim_x2, replace=TRUE))
    while(iter<iterations && loss_diff > 0.0001){  
      iter = iter+1
      for (cluster in 1:n_clusters){
        clusterMatrix = digitsx[, cluster_label==cluster]
        if (class(clusterMatrix)=='matrix'){
          cluster_mean[,cluster] = rowMeans(clusterMatrix)
          loss_dist[iter] = loss_dist[iter] + sum(colSums((clusterMatrix-cluster_mean[,cluster])^2))
        } else if (class(clusterMatrix)=='NULL'){
          #print(class(clusterMatrix))
          #print(dim(clusterMatrix))
          cluster_mean[,cluster] = digitsx[,random_sample]
          loss_dist[iter] = loss_dist[iter] + sum(colSums((clusterMatrix-cluster_mean[,cluster])^2))
        }
        else {
          #print(class(clusterMatrix))
          #print(dim(clusterMatrix))
          cluster_mean[,cluster] = clusterMatrix
        }
      }
      for (cluster in 1:n_clusters){
        cluster_dist[,cluster] = colSums((digitsx-c(cluster_mean[,cluster]))^2)
      }
      cluster_label = max.col(-cluster_dist)
      if (iter>1){
        loss_diff = abs(loss_dist[iter]-loss_dist[iter-1])
      }
    }
    minLoss[init] = loss_dist[iter]
    
    if (minLoss[init] == min(minLoss)){
      best_cluster_label = cluster_label
      best_cluster_mean = cluster_mean
      best_sequence_loss = loss_dist[1:iter]
    }
  }
  return (list("bcl"=best_cluster_label, "bcm"=best_cluster_mean, "bsl"=best_sequence_loss, "ml"=minLoss))
}

Part3

The stopping criteria used in KMeans while loop is checking the successive difference in loss values and setting a small threshold below which the algorithm is stopped.
